def show(img, title=None):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 15))
    ax.imshow(img)
    if title:
        ax.set_title(title)
    ax.set_xticks([])
    ax.set_yticks([])
    return fig, ax

filter = (stats_pred_data["area"]/stats_pred_data["convex_area"]) < 0.9

components_to_see = np.array(stats_pred_data[filter].index.astype(int))

mapa = np.zeros_like(components_pred_map)

shape_trees = components_pred_map.copy()

shape_trees[shape_trees>0] = 1


for num, idx in enumerate(components_to_see):
    bbox_0 = stats_pred_data.loc[idx, "bbox-0"]
    bbox_1 = stats_pred_data.loc[idx, "bbox-1"]
    bbox_2 = stats_pred_data.loc[idx, "bbox-2"]
    bbox_3 = stats_pred_data.loc[idx, "bbox-3"]

    pred_cut = shape_trees[bbox_0: bbox_2, bbox_1:bbox_3].copy()
    ortho_cut = ortho[bbox_0: bbox_2, bbox_1:bbox_3].copy()
    ortho_cut+= pred_cut*255*(2/10)

    mapa[bbox_0: bbox_2, bbox_1:bbox_3] = pred_cut
    
    fig, ax = show(ortho_cut)
    fig.suptitle(f"Razão: {stats_pred_data.loc[idx, 'area']/stats_pred_data.loc[idx,'convex_area']:.2f}")
    fig.set_size_inches(2,2)  
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

Como podemos ver, a partir de 0.85 a segmentação começa a ser feita de forma correta

Então, cortaremos qualquer label com $\frac{\text{area}}{\text{área convexa}} \leq 0.85$

components_to_iter = stats_pred_data.index.astype(int)

for idx in components_to_iter:

    count_tree_types =  np.unique(pred_map_99[components_pred_map == idx], return_counts=True)

    count_tree_types = pd.Series(count_tree_types[1], index=count_tree_types[0])

Construção do banco de labels¶

Adicionaremos ao conjunto as labels com alta confiança com base em nossas premissas.

Na construção do conjunto serão mantidas as árvore do conjunto de treino original

In [266]:
all_label_set = ground_truth_label.copy()

label_delta = np.zeros_like(all_label_set)

components_to_iter = stats_pred_data.index.astype(int)

for idx in components_to_iter:
    # se mais de 90% do componente é vazio será adicionado a nova amostra predita
    if np.mean(components_gt_label[components_pred_map==idx] == 0) > 0.9:
        class_count = np.unique(pred_map_99[components_pred_map==idx], return_counts=True)

        class_count = pd.Series(class_count[1], index=class_count[0]).sort_values(ascending=False)
        class_common = class_count.index[0]
        # print(class_common)
        all_label_set[components_pred_map==idx] = class_common
        label_delta[components_pred_map==idx] = class_common

Seleção das labels para manter balanceamento¶

In [274]:
def undersample(data, column_category):
    X = data.drop(column_category, axis=1).copy()
    y = data[column_category].copy()
    # define undersample strategy
    undersample_selector = RandomUnderSampler(sampling_strategy='majority', random_state=42)
    # fit and apply the transform
    X, y = undersample_selector.fit_resample(X, data[column_category])
    
    # summarize class distribution
    # columns_namem = X.columns.tolist()+[column_category]
    return pd.concat([X, y], axis=1)

Aplicando mapa de distâncias¶

In [285]:
from scipy.ndimage import distance_transform_edt
from scipy.ndimage import gaussian_filter
In [286]:
ref = label_for_next_iter.copy()

ref[ref>0] = 1
# generate the distance map
label_ref = label(ref)
new_lab = label_ref.copy()
# Aplica mapa de distância
new_lab = distance_transform_edt(new_lab)
# Aplica filtro gaussiano
new_lab = gaussian_filter(new_lab, sigma=5)

# substitui os valores de label_ref pelos valores de new_lab
save_lab = np.zeros(label_ref.shape)
for obj in np.unique(label_ref)[1:]:
    save_lab[label_ref==obj] = new_lab[label_ref==obj]/np.max(new_lab[label_ref==obj])
